      • createPlugin

        @NoException(value=true)
public IPluginV3 createPlugin(String name,
                                                       @Const
                                                       PluginFieldCollection fc,
                                                       @ByVal
                                                       nvinfer.TensorRTPhase phase)
        \brief Return a plugin object. Return nullptr in case of error.
        Parameters:
        name - A NULL-terminated name string of length 1024 or less, including the NULL terminator.
        fc - A pointer to a collection of fields needed for constructing the plugin.
        phase - The TensorRT phase in which the plugin is being created When the phase is TensorRTPhase::kRUNTIME, the PluginFieldCollection provided for serialization by the plugin's runtime interface will be passed as fc. \note The returned plugin object must be in an initialized state \note If invoked by the user (e.g. with TensorRTPhase::kBUILD, to add to the network defintion with addPluginV3()), it is the user's responsibility to delete the plugin object. If invoked by TensorRT (e.g. during engine deserialization), TensorRT will delete any objects it creates.
